'''iwlwifi''' is the wireless driver for [https://wireless.wiki.kernel.org/en/users/drivers/iwlwifi#introduction Intel's current wireless chips].

== Kernel == <!--T:3-->

<!--T:4-->
To make it work some kernel configuration is needed. The driver supports 802.11a/b/g/n/ac (depending on the device), so IEEE 802.11 should be enabled.

